##The first day Haidilao was back in business, the number of guests was a little pathetic

“

After all, Haidilao has been closed for 46 days, and in-store dining has been its most critical source of income.

”

On March 11, Haidilao announced on its Weibo account that from March 12, the first batch of 85 restaurants in 15 cities will resume operations and provide canteen services. Among the first batch of cities to restore their restaurants were Chengdu, Hangzhou, Foshan, Haikou, Nanjing and Xiamen, with the exception of Guangzhou and Shenzhen.

According to the list, interface news visited a number of Haidilao stores in Hangzhou, and all stores were closed at 10 hours, or 10 o'clock, instead of 24 hours.

Among them, lakeside Yintai shop due to exhaust fan problems on the first day to wait until pm to open. Haidilao Qingchun Road, which has not yet opened, told interface news that stores that are now open are in trial mode, with those that are not expected to open for trial on March 17.

Compared with the enthusiasm of people on social media platforms who "Miss Haidilao too much, " Haidilao on the first day of resuming dining seems a little cold.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Check in at the entrance of the store, photo: Zhang Qin

At present, all store admission requires consumers to show health code and temperature, spraying disinfectant, registration name and identity card number. In February, Haidilao, a restaurant in Changzhou, Jiangsu Province, where confirmed cases were reported, was once again open for eating, and was cautious in its efforts to prevent the disease.

Haidilao Tianhong shop staff told the Interface News, all stores are only open 40% of the area, the implementation of the next table to sit, small table only 1-2 people, large table to sit 2-4 people, many people need separate table. In addition to the normal temperature and disinfection procedures, the clerk has also increased the frequency with which he changes the sterilizing hot towels for consumers, the clerk said.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On each table stands a sign that says "this table has been disinfected, please feel free to sit down" . On the back of the sign are the name of the waiter for the day and the temperature of the day. On a screen inside the store, Haidilao pulled out a letter to customers, saying it was suspending kitchen visits, amusement parks, manicures and shoeshine. In addition, stores in Hangzhou sprayed disinfection water on the ground at 9 am, 2 pm, 5 pm and 8 pm.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the opening day, Haidilao stores introduced a companion gift, which includes hot pot dishes and Haidilao snacks, in addition to each table guests can receive an additional dessert. From the Menu, Bean Curd, fresh cut meat and seafood and other items in many stores show "clear" status, the staff said these dishes supply chain, logistics is still limited.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Shrimp cakes from Haidilao Jiuyicheng store. Photo: Zhang Qin

"today is the first day of business after the outbreak in Haidilao, " a shop assistant at Yintai Haidilao, west of Hangzhou, told interface news. "The company didn't do much promotion except on Weibo. I don't think guests know yet. There should be no line today. There will be more guests at dinner time. "

At 11:30 that day, the store only served six small tables and one medium table.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Haidilao Jiuyicheng store. PICTURE: Zhang Qin

Although nearly every store has far more employees than sitting customers, Haidilao has not yet returned to work in batches, interface news has learned from several stores.

"before this, many old customers who had added Wechat came today. Before this, I started my vacation on January 10th. Halfway through my vacation, the company informed me that I could not go to work for the time being, and I had not eaten hotpot for more than 50 days. " A Haidilao shop assistant expressed his feelings about returning to work to interface news.

The employee revealed that during the 46-day suspension of Haidilao Canteen, the company paid only the guaranteed amount of wages.

The news that Haidilao is back on the market has given many investors a sigh of relief.

Shares in Haidilao rose 1.18 per cent to HK $34.30 after the low-key announcement yesterday, compared with a closing price of HK $29.70 on the last trading day of the year, on January 24. However, the enthusiasm for capital quickly waned, with Haidilao shares down 5.96 per cent from yesterday's close to HK $32.35 as of press time, down from HK $31.70 during the period.

After all, Haidilao has been closed for 46 days, and in-store dining has been its most critical source of income. According to a research report issued earlier by CITIC Construction Investment, its estimate of the epidemic is about 5.04 billion yuan lost from Haidilao's revenue in 2020, and about 580 million yuan lost from the net profit of Guimu.

The move follows the suspension of its mainland stores and delivery services from January 26 to 31. On February 2, Haidilao announced that it would continue to extend the closure of its mainland stores in light of the recent outbreak until yesterday, when it finally announced the resumption of business after 46 days of suspension.

In order to avoid cash flow cut-off, Haidilao also closed during the time to do take-out, fresh community distribution and semi-finished food business.

On February 15, Haidilao, which has received community group purchase and distribution, announced the resumption of delivery services in some stores and the upgrade of delivery services to contactless delivery "safe delivery" , and the temporary suspension of boiler rental and in-house services. On March 3, Haidilao launched its own series of semi-finished dishes on several e-commerce platforms such as Haidilao APP.

But the above-mentioned self-help measures are not fully open, involving shops and cities are limited, not to mention the delivery business is only a drop in the ocean. In the first half of 2019, Haidilao's revenue was 188 million yuan, up 40.9 percent year on year, accounting for only 1.6 percent of the total turnover. The takeout business alone is clearly not going to sustain it.

But on Feb. 22, Haidilao received 2.1 billion yuan in credit from the Beijing branch of Citic Bank and Baixin Bank. This cooperation, for the latter initiative contact, the two sides since February 12 began to discuss loan-related matters.
